claim: Flublok (quadrivalent) was evaluated in the pivotal trial against Fluarix (quadrivalent standard-dose vaccine).
explanation: A multi‐panel figure of hemagglutination inhibition (HI) titers (log₂ scale) against four influenza strains (A/H3N2, A/H1N1pdm09, B/Vic, B/Yam) measured at Day 0 and 1 month in two age cohorts (18–44 years and 45–64 years), each tested against egg‐grown and cell‐grown virus. Box‐and‐whisker plots with overlaid individual data points are shown. Colored symbols indicate different vaccine sequences (generic codes: ccliIV4, RIV4, IIIV4) in a crossover design, with p-values denoting statistical comparisons. The figure shows immunogenicity data for generic vaccine codes (RIV4, IIIV4, ccliIV4) in a crossover design but does not explicitly identify Flublok (quadrivalent) or Fluarix (quadrivalent standard‐dose) by name, nor a pivotal head-to-head comparison between them, and thus does not support the claim Note: Legend text is small and generic codes are used; brand names are not visible
